OL,3,CDrink and drug driving spot checks to
OL,4,Ctake place during Euros
OL,6,FDrink and drug driving typically
OL,7,Fincreases during major sporting
OL,8,Ftournaments.
OL,10,FAccording to Road Safety North East,
OL,11,Fthere was an increase in drink and
OL,12,Fdrug driving injuries in the region on
OL,13,Fthe day of and the day following
OL,14,FEngland's matches during the World Cup
OL,15,Fin 2022. On these days, drink/drug
OL,16,Fdriving injuries increased from 12% to
OL,17,F16% of all injuries, while those
OL,18,Fresulting in serious injury rose from
OL,19,F15% to 20%.
